**`resolve_oid` accepts pure-numeric strings as hex OID prefixes.** A string like `"3"` or `"42"` passes the `is_hex` check (all chars are hex digits) and falls through to prefix matching against known OIDs. This means if a user types `forge issue show 3` intending to look up display ID `3`, but the index is empty or stale, it silently resolves to whatever OID happens to start with `3` — which could be a completely unrelated entity.

The index lookup is tried first, but only when `index` is `Some` and has a matching key. If the index ref doesn't exist yet (fresh repo, first issue), `read_index` returns `None`, and the display ID `"3"` silently falls through to hex prefix matching. This is a correctness hazard: the behavior of `forge issue show 3` changes depending on whether the index has been written yet.